Here's the Java implementation:

```java
public class PowerOfThree {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        int exponent = 0;
        while (n > 0 && (n & 1) == 0) {
            n >>>= 1;
            exponent++;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

Explanation:

1. Initialize the exponent to 0.
2. While the number is greater than zero and its least significant bit is zero, shift the number right by one and increment the exponent.
3. Return true if the number becomes one, otherwise false.

The time complexity of this solution is O(log3(n)), where log3(n) is the number of times we need to divide n by 3 to get 1. The space complexity is O(1).

